n\n<p>When applying for a goods vehicle operator&rsquo;s licence, you&rsquo;ll have to pay:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a one-off fee payable on application</li>\n  <li>a fee for the issue of a licence</li>\n  <li>a fee for the issue of an interim licence (if applicable)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll then have to pay a continuation fee every 5 years to keep your licence active.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Application for a licence</td>\n      <td>£254</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Issue of a licence</td>\n      <td>£397</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Continuation of a licence after 5 years</td>\n      <td>£397</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Issue of an interim licence</td>\n      <td>£68</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Major change to a licence</td>\n      <td>£254</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>How to pay</h2>\n\n<p>You can pay your fees:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>online</strong> - you will need to register first for the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.tan.gov.uk/Operator/AuthFiles/VOSA_Login.asp?\" title=\"OLSS\">VOSA Operator Licensing Self-Service System (<abbr title=\"Operator Licensing Self-Service System\">OLSS</abbr>)</a></li>\n  <li><strong>by phone</strong> - call the VOSA Helpline on <strong>0300 123 9000</strong> to pay for the interim, issuing and continuation fees</li>\n  <li><strong>by post</strong> - cheques should be made payable to &lsquo;VOSA&rsquo; and sent to the following address </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nCentral Licensing Office\n<br />Hillcrest House\n<br />386 Harehills Lane\n<br />Leeds LS9 6NF\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/being-a-goods-vehicle-operator/operating-centres","slug":"operating-centres","order":5,"title":"Operating centres","body":"<p>Your operating centre is where your vehicles are normally kept when not in use. When you apply for an operator&rsquo;s licence, you&rsquo;ll be asked to give the address of your proposed centre(s) and information about the numbers of trailers and vehicles you will keep there.</p>\n\n<p>When you apply for an operator’s licence, you’ll need to show that your operating centre:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>is large enough</li>\n  <li>has safe access</li>\n  <li>is in an environmentally acceptable location</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you don’t own the operating centre, you must show that you’re allowed to use it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Advertising your application for a goods vehicle operator&rsquo;s licence</h2>\n\n<p>You must advertise your application for a licence in a local newspaper and supply details of your proposed operating centre. This advertisement must appear at least once in the period from 21 days before to 21 days after you make your application, to give people the chance to object. </p>\n\n<p>Your application may be refused if you don&rsquo;t advertise the centre properly. </p>\n\n<p>Find more information on how to advertise your application for a goods vehicle operator licence.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/GV79Annex%20A%20-%20advert.pdf\" title=\"Download ‘GV79 - Annex A: advertise your application for an operator licence’ (PDF, 81KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘GV79 - Annex A: advertise your application for an operator licence’ (PDF, 81KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/GV%2081%20Advice%20Note%20-%20Additional%20Guidance%20on%20Advertising.pdf\" title=\"Download ‘GV81– additional guidance on advertising’ (PDF, 35KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘GV81– additional guidance on advertising’ (PDF, 35KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Objecting to an application for a goods vehicle operator licence</h2>\n\n<p>Local councils, planning authorities, police, trade associations, trade unions and other bodies may object to your application for a licence.</p>\n\n<p>Objections may be made on the grounds of:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your fitness to operate</li>\n  <li>your financial arrangements</li>\n  <li>your professional competence </li>\n  <li>the environmental impact of the operating centre</li>\n  <li>the general suitability of the centre</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Your operating centre will need to meet certain conditions and not interfere with any local amenities. Certain things will be taken into account, like:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>its effect on the surrounding environment</li>\n  <li>planning permissions or applications relating to the centre or the land near it</li>\n  <li>the number, type and size of vehicles using the centre</li>\n  <li>where and how vehicles will park</li>\n  <li>how often and for what purpose the centre will be used</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Read further information about the environmental impact of operating centres and how to object to a proposed centre. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/GV74B%20Guide.pdf\" title=\"Download ‘GV74B – goods vehicle operators guide to making objections and complaints’ (PDF, 74KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘GV74B – goods vehicle operators guide to making objections and complaints’ (PDF, 74KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/GV74R%20Guide.pdf\" title=\"Download ‘GV74R – guide to making representations and complaints’ (PDF, 82KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘GV74R – guide to making representations and complaints’ (PDF, 82KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/GV79E%20Application%20for%20licence%20-%20Environmental%20Information%20.pdf\" title=\"Download ‘GV79E – supplementary environmental information’ (PDF, 50KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘GV79E – supplementary environmental information’ (PDF, 50KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/being-a-goods-vehicle-operator/maintaining-your-vehicles","s