s</h2>\n\n<p>A licence to drive lorries, minibuses or buses is valid until aged 45. After 45, the driver must renew every 5 years until they&rsquo;re 65. After 65 they must renew their licence every year.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The rules for lorry and bus driving licences are changing from 19 January 2013. Licences issued from this date are all valid for 5 years, up to age 65.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Qualifications for lorry, bus and coach drivers</h2>\n\n<p>As well as a valid licence, professional lorry, bus and coach drivers also need to hold a <a href=\"/driver-certificate-of-professional-competence-cpc/\" title=\"Find out how to get a driver CPC qualification\">Driver Certificate of Professional Competence (CPC)</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Tachographs</h2>\n\n<p>Some drivers you employ need to record their journeys on <a href=\"/tachographs\" title=\"tachographs\">tachographs</a> to make sure they are following the <a href=\"/drivers-hours\" title=\"rules on drivers' hours\">rules on drivers&rsquo; hours</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Driver entitlement checking service</h2>\n\n<p>The driver entitlement checking service lets you check with <abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> that the information on a driver&rsquo;s licence is correct. You can check:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the licence validity dates</li>\n  <li>the categories of vehicle that the driver can drive</li>\n  <li>if there are any current endorsements on the licence</li>\n  <li>if the driver is disqualified</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The driver must give permission for the check to take place.</p>\n\n<p>There are a number of ways to use the service.</p>\n\n<h3>Electronic checking service</h3>\n\n<p>The Electronic Driver Entitlement Checking Service (<abbr title=\"Electronic Driver Entitlement Checking Service\">EDECS</abbr>) is a secure online service that gives you an answer the next working day. To use the service your company will need to pass accreditation checks and enter into a contract with <abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr>. </p>\n\n<p>Organisations pay any set-up costs and there is a cost of £1.50 per enquiry.</p>\n\n<p>For more information about <abbr title=\"Electronic Driver Entitlement Checking Service\">EDECS</abbr> email <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#100;&#101;&#099;&#115;&#064;&#100;&#118;&#108;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#100;&#101;&#099;&#115;&#064;&#100;&#118;&#108;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>By post</h3>\n\n<p>You can also check a driver’s entitlement to drive by post. Each enquiry costs £5.</p>\n\n<p>For more information about the postal service email <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#100;&#114;&#105;&#118;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#095;&#102;&#112;&#101;&#064;&#100;&#118;&#108;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#100;&#114;&#105;&#118;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#095;&#102;&#112;&#101;&#064;&#100;&#118;&#108;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>By phone</h3>\n\n<p>You can also check a driver’s entitlement to drive by phoning <abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> on <strong>0906 139 3837</strong>. </p>\n\n<p>The driver must provide consent for the enquiry. They can do this by calling <strong>0300 790 6801</strong> before you call, or they can be with you when you call <abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>Lines are open Monday to Friday 8am to 7pm and Saturday 8am to 2pm. Calls cost 51p per minute.</p>\n\n<h3>By fax</h3>\n\n<p>This service provides a yes or no answer by fax. It’s available to vehicle finance organisations that suspect a fraudulent driving licence has been used.</p>\n\n<p>Each enquiry costs £5.</p>\n\n<p>For more information about the fax service email <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#100;