us special licensing rules in London.</p>\n\n<h3>Standard licence - national operations only</h3>\n\n<p>If you apply for a standard licence you can only operate within Great Britain. Most full-time commercial operators use standard licences.</p>\n\n<h3>Standard licence - national and international operations</h3>\n\n<p>This kind of licence lets you take passengers abroad as well as within Great Britain.</p>\n\n<h3>Restricted licence</h3>\n\n<p>You can only apply for a restricted licence for small-scale operations. They allow you to use 1 or 2 vehicles, and neither can carry more than 8 passengers.</p>\n\n<p>You can carry up to 16 passengers in either vehicle if you don&rsquo;t use it as part of a passenger transport business, or you&rsquo;re operating your vehicles as a sideline and not as your main job.</p>\n\n<h3>Special restricted licence</h3>\n\n<p>Special restricted licences are used to operate a licensed taxi on a local service. You can only apply for this licence if you&rsquo;re a licensed taxi operator. A local service is one where:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>stops are no more than 24.15 kilometres (15 miles) apart</li>\n  <li>at least one stop is within the area of the district council that issued your taxi or private hire vehicle (PHV) licence.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The service must be registered with the local <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/topics/tpm/traffic-commissioners\" title=\"Traffic Commissioner\">Traffic Commissioner.</a></p>\n\n<h3>Licensing in London</h3>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a London Service Permit to <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.tfl.gov.uk/businessandpartners/busoperators/1228.aspx\" title=\"run a private bus or coach service in London\">run a private bus or coach service in London.</a></p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.tfl.gov.uk/businessandpartners/taxisandprivatehire/2807.aspx\" title=\"Taxis and private hire services in London\">Taxis and private hire services in London</a> are licensed by Transport for London (<abbr title=\"Transport for London\">TfL</abbr>).</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/psv-operator-licences/how-to-apply-for-a-psv-licence","slug":"how-to-apply-for-a-psv-licence","order":2,"title":"How to apply for a PSV licence","body":"<h2>Standard and restricted licences</h2>\n\n<p>You can apply for a <abbr title=\"Public Service Vehicle\">PSV</abbr> licence using form PSV421. The address to send it to is on the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Application%20for%20a%20PSV%20Operators%20Licence%20(PSV%20421).pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV421: Application to a Traffic Commissioner for a Public Service Vehicle Operator's Licence' (PDF, 198KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV421, Application to a Traffic Commissioner for a Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence’ (PDF, 198KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You need to prove that you have the financial resources to maintain your vehicles properly.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/PSV421%20-%20Annex%20A%20financial%20levels.pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV421, Annex A, financial levels' (PDF, 11KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV421, Annex A, financial levels’ (PDF, 11KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You must sign an agreement with a garage or agent for safety inspections and repair of vehicles and trailers.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/PSV421%20-%20Annex%20C%20Maintenance%20contract.pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV421, Annex C, maintenance contract' (PDF, 16KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV421, Annex C, maintenance contract’ (PDF, 16KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Guidance notes</h3>\n\n<p>There are detailed guidance notes on leaflet PSV421G to help you fill in your application correctly.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Application%20for%20a%20PSV%20Operators%20Licence%20-%20Guidance%20notes%20(PSV%20421G).pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV421G, Guidance notes to help you complete your application for a Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence' (PDF, 175KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV421G, Guidance notes to help you complete your application for a Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence’ (PDF, 175KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Special restricted licences for taxi and private hire vehicle operators</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a licensed taxi (Hackney Carriage) or private hire vehicle operator you can apply for a special restricted <abbr title=\"Public Service Vehicle\">PSV</abbr> operator licence using form PSV356. The address to send it to is on the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Special%20Restricted%20PSV%20Operators%20Licence%20Application%20(PSV%20356).pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV356, Application to a Traffic Commissioner for a Special Restricted Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence' (PDF, 48KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV356, Application to a Traffic Commissioner for a Special Restricted Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence’ (PDF, 48KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Guidance notes</h3>\n\n<p>There are detailed guidance notes on leaflet PSV356G to help you fill in your application correctly.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Special%20licence%20guidance%20notes%20(PSV%20356G).pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV356G, Guidance notes to help you complete your application for a Special Restricted Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence' (PDF, 21KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV356G, Guidance notes to help you complete your application for a Special Restricted Public Service Vehicle Operator’s Licence’ (PDF, 21KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>When to apply</h2>\n\n<p>Whatever the type of licence, you should apply at least 9 weeks before you need your licence. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>It’s illegal to operate your vehicles before a licence has been issued.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Getting your licence</h2>\n\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve got your licence it won&rsquo;t have an expiry date, but you&rsquo;ll be asked to confirm your details every 5 years. The Traffic Commissioner&rsquo;s Office will get in touch with you to check them. If you&rsquo;ve got a special restricted (taxi) licence, you&rsquo;ll need to pay a continuation fee.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The Traffic Commissioner can suspend or revoke your licence if they suspect you’ve been breaking its terms.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You must also tell the Traffic Commissioner <a href=\"/psv-operator-licences/making-changes-to-your-psv-licence\" title=\"if your circumstances change\">if your circumstances change</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Fees</h2>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Type of licence</th>\n      <th>Fees</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Application for a standard licence</td>\n      <td>£206</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Application for a restricted licence</td>\n      <td>£206</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><a href=\"/psv-operator-licences/making-changes-to-your-psv-licence\" title=\"Variation of a licence\">Variation of a licence</a></td>\n      <td>£121</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Application for a special restricted (taxi) licence</td>\n      <td>£61</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Continuation fee for a special restricted (taxi) licence (payable every 5 years)</td>\n      <td>£61</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Ways you can pay</h2>\n\n<p>You can pay for your licence online, by phone or by post.</p>\n\n<h3>Paying online</h3>\n\n<p>You can pay online by <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.tan.gov.uk/tanen/vosa_registerform.asp\" title=\"register for operator licensing self-service system\">registering for the <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> operator licensing self-service system.</a></p>\n\n<h3>Payin