<p>The route can be any length, as long as passengers can get off within 15 miles of where they got on.</p>\n\n<p>With <a href=\"/run-local-bus-service/exemptions\" title=\"Exemptions\">a few exceptions</a> local services operating outside London must be registered with the local <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/topics/tpm/traffic-commissioners\" title=\"Traffic commissioners\">traffic commissioner.</a></p>\n\n<p>To <a href=\"/run-local-bus-service/register-a-bus-service-in-london\" title=\"Register a bus services in London\">run a service in London</a> you need a London Service Permit.</p>\n\n<h2>Who can register</h2>\n<p>You can register a local bus service if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>hold a valid <a href=\"/psv-operator-licences\" title=\"PSV operator licences\">PSV operator&rsquo;s licence</a></li>\n  <li>hold a community bus permit</li>\n  <li>are a local education authority and want to register a school bus service using your own vehicles</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Taxi or private hire vehicle owners can also register by getting a <a href=\"/psv-operator-licences\" title=\"special PSV operator licences\">special PSV operator’s licence</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Before you register</h2>\n<p>Before registering a local bus service you should consider if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your route is suitable</li>\n  <li>you have the right sort of vehicles</li>\n  <li>you can keep to the timetable given the traffic conditions on route</li>\n  <li>you have enough drivers to cover absences though sicknesses, holidays, etc</li>\n  <li>you have replacement vehicles if other vehicles are off-road</li>\n  <li>there are any traffic regulation conditions – contact your <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/topics/tpm/traffic-commissioners\" title=\"local traffic area office contact details\">local traffic area office</a></li>\n  <li>a Quality Partnership or Quality Contract Scheme exists - contact your <a href=\"/find-your-local-council\" title=\"Find your local council\">local transport authority</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You’ll have to run the service just as you have registered it, even if staff members are ill or a vehicle is off the road. There are <a href=\"/run-local-bus-service/penalties-for-poor-service\" title=\"Penalties for poor service\">penalties</a> if you don’t.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/run-local-bus-service/how-to-register","slug":"how-to-register","order":2,"title":"How to register","body":"<p>You must give the traffic commissioner at least 56 days notice of your intention to start a bus service. This notice period begins on the day when the traffic commissioner accepts your application.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Holders of a ‘Section 22’ community bus permit must give at least 28 days notice.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you want to start the service sooner you must complete a supplementary form. The traffic commissioner decides whether or not to agree to this.</p>\n\n<p>There are additional requirements for planned services in Scotland.</p>\n\n<h2>Fees</h2>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Type of service</th>\n      <th>Fee</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Local bus service</td>\n      <td>£60</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Community bus service</td>\n      <td>£13</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Apply online</h2>\n<p>You can register through the electronic bus service registration (EBSR) system. Contact the helpline for information on how to do this.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Vehicle and Operator Services Agency (<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>) helpline</strong></p>\n\n<p>0300 123 9000 <br />\nMonday to Friday, 7:30am to 6pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Apply by post</h2>\n<p>Download the application form for the type of service you want to run:</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/A