/p>\n\n<p>You don’t need to register a service if the only passengers who pay fares are either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>studying at a school or college</li>\n  <li>supervising pupils or students</li>\n  <li>teachers or assistants working at the school or college</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If other people can also use the service, it must be registered.</p>\n\n<h2>Other exemptions</h2>\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need to register:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a replacement bus service - when a train service is temporarily cancelled and a bus is used instead</li>\n  <li>excursions or tours - as long as they operate less than once a week</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/run-local-bus-service/traffic-regulation-conditions","slug":"traffic-regulation-conditions","order":5,"title":"Traffic regulation conditions","body":"<p>The local council can ask the traffic commissioner to impose conditions on your licence. They may do this to: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>reduce dangers to other road users </li>\n  <li>reduce traffic congestion </li>\n  <li>limit environmental pollution </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The conditions could affect: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your bus routes</li>\n  <li>where you can stop </li>\n  <li>when you can stop and for how long </li>\n  <li>where you can turn or reverse</li>\n  <li>the number of vehicles, their type or their frequency </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>In some cases the conditions will start straight away.</p>\n\n<h2>You can&rsquo;t meet the conditions</h2>\n\n<p>If you can&rsquo;t run your service under the conditions, you must <a href=\"/run-local-bus-service/changing-or-cancelling-a-bus-service\" title=\"changing or cancelling a bus service\">change the registration</a> within 28 days. You won’t have to pay a fee if you change the registration because of these conditions. </p>\n\n<h2>You disagree with the conditions</h2>\n<p>If you disagree with the traffic commissioner’s decision you can ask for a public inquiry within 28 days. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>It’s against the law to disobey traffic regulation conditions.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/run-local-bus-service/penalties-for-poor-service","slug":"penalties-for-poor-service","order":6,"title":"Penalties for poor service","body":"<p>Once you have registered your service you must run it:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>at the times you&rsquo;ve said it would run</li>\n  <li>along the route you&rsquo;ve registered</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Penalties</h2>\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t run a reliable or punctual service the traffic commissioner can stop you from running the service - or even running any services at all.</p>\n\n<p>The traffic commissioner can also fine you. The size of the fine is based on the number of vehicles you&rsquo;re licensed to use.</p>\n\n<p>If you provide the local bus service in England and Wales, you may also have to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>spend money on providing or improving local services or facilities</li>\n  <li>compensate passengers</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you disagree with the traffic commissioner’s decision you can appeal to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/tribunals/aa\" title=\"Upper Tribunal\">Upper Tribunal.</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/PD%20Standards%20for%20local%20buses.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Practice direction: Standards for local bus services' (PDF, 38KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Practice direction: Standards for local bus services’ (PDF, 38KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/run-local-bus-service/register-a-bus-service-in-london","slug":"register-a-bus-service-in-london","order":7,"title":"Register a bus service in London","body":"<p>To run a bus service in London you must have a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.tfl.gov.uk/businessandpartners/busoperators/1228.aspx\" title=\"Apply for a London Service Permit\">London Service Permit</a>. Permits last for 5 years and you must normally apply at least 3 months before starti