ce to the general public where:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>at least half the seats are available to and regularly used by them</li>\n  <li>bus stops are in places where people are likely to use them reasonably often</li>\n  <li>if there aren&rsquo;t fixed stopping places, the arrangements for letting passengers on and off mean people are likely to use them reasonably often</li>\n  <li>single journey fares are reasonably priced</li>\n  <li>they can pay fares conveniently</li>\n  <li>the bus doesn&rsquo;t have any sign or other indication that it&rsquo;s not available to them</li>\n  <li>information about the service, its route and timetable is accessible to them</li>\n  <li>if it&rsquo;s a flexible service, where passengers book in advance, these arrangements mustn&rsquo;t deter people who want to make a single journey</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If your bus service is intended for transporting pupils or the disabled or elderly there are slightly different conditions.</p>\n\n<h2>Further information</h2>\n\n<p>For England and Wales, contact the Bus Service Operator&rsquo;s Grant helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>BSOG helpline</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#098;&#115;&#111;&#103;&#064;&#100;&#102;&#116;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#098;&#115;&#111;&#103;&#064;&#100;&#102;&#116;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a> <br />\n020 7944 8588</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Scotland has its own helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Bus Service Operator’s Grant helpline (Scotland)</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#098;&#115;&#111;&#103;&#064;&#116;&#114;&#097;&#110;&#115;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#115;&#099;&#111;&#116;&#108;&#097;&#110;&#100;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#098;&#115;&#111;&#103;&#064;&#116;&#114;&#097;&#110;&#115;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#115;&#099;&#111;&#116;&#108;&#097;&