ov.uk/set-up-run-motorcycle-approved-training-body-atb/overview","slug":"overview","order":1,"title":"Overview","body":"<p>You must be an approved training body (<abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr>) with the Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>) to provide:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>compulsory basic training (<abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr>) for learner motorcyclists</li>\n  <li>direct access scheme (<abbr title=\"Direct access scheme\">DAS</abbr>) training to riders learning to ride a large motorcycle </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> and <abbr title=\"Direct access scheme\">DAS</abbr> training must be given by instructors certified by the Driving Standards Agency working for your approved training body.</p>\n\n<p>The sites you use to provide training from must also be approved by the <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/set-up-run-motorcycle-approved-training-body-atb/rules-for-being-an-atb","slug":"rules-for-being-an-atb","order":2,"title":"Rules for being an ATB","body":"<p>To be an approved training body (<abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr>) you must meet certain rules. </p>\n\n<h2>&lsquo;Fit and proper&rsquo;</h2>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You must be a ‘fit and proper’ person to run the <abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>When deciding if you&rsquo;re a &lsquo;fit and proper&rsquo; person, the Driving Standards Agency will look at if you have:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>had any convictions in the last 4 years</li>\n  <li>any motoring convictions</li>\n  <li>been disqualified from driving</li>\n  <li>any penalty points on your licence</li>\n  <li>any court proceedings pending against you  </li>\n  <li>any penalty points on your licence </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Training</h2>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>As an <abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr> you must provide compulsory basic training (<abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr>). Any <abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> and direct access scheme (<abbr title=\"Direct access scheme\">DAS</abbr>) courses you provide must meet the legal requirements.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> syllabus gives full details on what must be provided. The <abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr>  and <abbr title=\"Direct access scheme\">DAS</abbr> guidance also give best practice.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/publications/dsa-national-driving-riding-standards/dsa-cbt-syllabus-guidance-notes.pdf\" title=\"Download 'CBT syllabus and guidance notes' (PDF, 115KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> syllabus and guidance notes’ (PDF, 115KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/publications/dsa-national-driving-riding-standards/dsa-direct-access-scheme-das-guidance-notes.pdf\" title=\"Download 'DAS motorcycle training guidance' (PDF, 109KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Direct access scheme\">DAS</abbr> motorcycle training guidance’ (PDF, 109KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>An instructor is only allowed to supervise up to 2 trainees during on-road tuition.</p>\n\n<p>Your instructors must be in radio contact with all trainees  at all times during on-road tuition.</p>\n\n<h2>Training sites</h2>\n\n<p>You must have the use of a suitable site or sites for training in the off-road parts of the <abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> course. </p>\n\n<p>These sites must be <a href=\"apply-for-cbt-site-authorisation\" title=\"Apply for CBT site authorisation\">authorised by the Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>)</a> before they&rsquo;re used.</p>\n\n<h2>Instructors</h2>\n\n<p>You must make sure that all your instructors have a valid instructor certificate for the type of training they give. This must show the name of your <abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>At least 1 of your instructors must have successfully completed the <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>’s <a href=\"/become-dsa-assessed-cbt-motorcycle-instructor\" title=\"Become a DSA assessed CBT motorcycle instructor\">assessment course for motorcycle training</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>-assessed instructors are allowed to train other people that you want  to appoint as instructors - this is known as &lsquo;down-training&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>You should have at least 1 <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>-assessed instructor for every 10 instructors that have been down-trained. </p>\n\n<h2>Monitoring</h2>\n\n<p>You should send all required information about the courses you provide to <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>reporting any incidents</li>\n  <li>dates when you&rsquo;re providing <abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> courses</li>\n  <li>the <abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr> certificates of completion you issue</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr> manual gives more details about what you have to send.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/dsa-bl/dsa-atb-manual.pdf\" title=\"Download 'ATB manual' (PDF, 190KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Approved training body\">ATB</abbr> manual’ (PDF, 190KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/set-up-run-motorcycle-approved-training-body-atb/apply-to-become-an-atb","slug":"apply-to-become-an-atb","order":3,"title":"Apply to become an ATB","body":"<p>To apply to register an approved training body (<ab