) course must be authorised by the Driving Standards Agency (<abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>).  </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You can’t use a site until you’ve got authorisation from <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>To apply for authorisation, download the application form and send it to <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://assets.dft.gov.uk/dsa-bl/dsa-cbt-site-inspection-form2.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Request for site inspection for compulsory basic training' (PDF, 20KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Request for site inspection for compulsory basic training’ (PDF, 20KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also need to include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a written permission letter, signed by the site owner on official letter headed paper</li>\n  <li>a draft plan of the intended site, eg an annotated satellite image</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n\n<br /><abbr title=\"Compulsory basic training\">CBT</abbr>\n<br />Driving Standards Agency\n<br />The Axis Building\n<br />112 Upper Parliament Street\n<br />Nottingham\n<br />NG1 6LP\n<br />\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Site inspection</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> will:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>inspect the site</li>\n  <li>send a site report to you</li>\n  <li>send a unique site code to you if the site is suitable</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The site report will explain any rules set by <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr>. This will include how many trainees are allowed on the site. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You should make sure all your instructors are aware of these details.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Changes to authorised sites</h2>\n\n<p>You must tell <abbr title=\"Driving Standards Agency\">DSA</abbr> straight away if a site is altered or added to.</p>\n\n<p>Download