a nominated technician, not to a centre - this means that only the individual who has the card can use it. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you’re the nominated technician and you work at 2 workshops, you’ll need a card for each workshop.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>Fill out an application form D778B and send it to the Vehicle and Operator Services Agency (<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>), where your application will be checked and approved. It will then be forwarded to the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (<abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr>), who will issue your card to the <abbr title=\"Approved Tachograph Centre\">ATC</abbr> where you work.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need a PIN code to use a workshop card. This will be sent to your home address, and must only be used by you.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Application%20for%20a%20digital%20tachograph%20workshop%20card.pdf\" title=\"Download 'D778B: Application for a digital tachograph workshop card' (PDF, 372KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘D778B: Application for a digital tachograph workshop card’ (PDF, 372KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Before you fill in the application form, read &lsquo;How to fill in your application for a digital tachograph workshop card (D778B)&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"https://www.dvla.gov.uk/dvla/forms/~/media/pdf/leaflets/INF178B.ashx\" title=\"Download 'How to fill in your application for a digital tachograph workshop card (D778B)' (PDF, 211KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘How to fill in your application for a digital tachograph workshop card (D778B)’ (PDF, 211KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>For more help, contact the <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> helpline</strong> <br />\n0300 123 9000</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Working with tachograph workshop cards</h2>\n\n<p>Workshop cards can hold:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>details of 88 calibrations</li>\n  <li>a small amount of events and faults data</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Cards should be used as a driver card during any road tests related to tachograph work. This means that calibration details, periodic inspection details and any subsequent road test can be recorded together and downloaded to give a complete record of each vehicle&rsquo;s activities.</p>\n\n<p>A workshop card must not be used instead of a company card. If you have a card used by your calibration centre, this must only be used in accordance with the tachograph centre&rsquo;s duties and not as a substitute company card.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>All insertions of a card are recorded on the vehicle unit and the card.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Renewal of workshop cards</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> sends a renewal list to <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> 2 months before a card’s expiry. This is then checked and returned to the <abbr title=\"Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency\">DVLA</abbr> with details of technicians whose cards can be renewed.</p>\n\n<p>You must report any lost or stolen cards to <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> and the police immediately.</p>\n\n<p>If your card develops a fault or is lost or stolen, you can apply for a replacement by sending a D778B application form to <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>. You&rsquo;ll need to provide a police incident reference number for stolen cards.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Any misuse of workshop cards may lead to the withdrawal of your nominated technician and tachograph centre’s approval.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-29T12:50:47+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Driving and t