approval. Normally, the manufacturer or importer will take care of this.</p>\n\n<p>However, your vehicle might not have approval, and you might need to apply for it. Examples of when this might happen include if you&rsquo;ve:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/vehicle-registration/kit-cars-and-rebuilds\" title=\"Kit cars and rebuilds\">built or rebuilt</a> a vehicle</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/vehicle-registration/radically-altered-vehicles\" title=\"Radically altered vehicles\">radically altered</a> a vehicle</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/vehicle-registration/reconstructed-classic-vehicles\" title=\"Reconstructed classic vehicles\">reconstructed a classic vehicle</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/importing-vehicles-into-the-uk/mutual-recognition\" title=\"Importing your vehicle\">imported</a> a vehicle</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Exemptions</h2>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t need vehicle approval for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>cars and light goods vehicles over 10 years old</li>\n  <li>heavy goods vehicles over 25 years old</li>\n  <li>tracked vehicles, eg a vehicle that runs on tracks rather than wheels</li>\n  <li>vehicles made specifically for use on construction sites, quarries, ports and airports</li>\n  <li>vehicles made specifically for and used by the armed services, fire and rescue forces, or used in maintaining public order</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If your vehicle needs approval, you must send proof of this in when you apply to <a href=\"/vehicle-registration\" title=\"Register your vehicle\">register it</a>. If you don&rsquo;t, the <abbr title=\"Driver &amp; Vehicle Licensing Authority\">DVLA</abbr> won&rsquo;t register your vehicle.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/vehicle-approval/individual-vehicle-approval","slug":"individual-vehicle-approval","order":3,"title":"Individual Vehicle Approval","body":"<h2>Who can use the scheme?</h2>\n\n<p>You can use the Individual Vehicle Approval (<abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr>) scheme if you&rsquo;re making or importing a single vehicle or a very small number of vehicles in the following categories:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>passenger cars</li>\n  <li>light goods vehicles (up to 3,500kg)</li>\n  <li>buses and coaches</li>\n  <li>medium to heavy goods vehicles (more than 3,500kg)</li>\n  <li>trailers</li>\n  <li>special purpose vehicles, eg vehicles specially designed to hold a wheelchair</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can’t use the Statutory <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> scheme if your vehicle has been registered before in the UK - you’ll need to use <a href=\"voluntary-approval\" title=\"Voluntary approval\">Voluntary <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr></a> instead.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Vehicle identification number</h2>\n\n<p>Your vehicle needs a <a href=\"/vehicle-registration/vehicle-identification-number\" title=\"Vehicle identification number\">vehicle identification number</a> (<abbr title=\"Vehicle Identification Number\">VIN</abbr>) before having an <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> inspection. If it doesn’t have one, apply to your <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/dvla/contactus/localoffices/findnear.aspx\" title=\"Find your local DVLA office\">local <abbr title=\"Driver &amp; Vehicle Licensing Authority\">DVLA</abbr> office.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Basic and normal <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>There are 2 levels of <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> inspection: basic and normal.</p>\n\n<h3>Basic <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr></h3>\n\n<p>Basic <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> involves a visual inspection and other tests to make sure the vehicle meets the necessary standards. You won&rsquo;t normally need to provide any documentary evidence.</p>\n\n<p>You can apply if you have a passenger car or light goods vehicle in one of these categories:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>left-hand drive vehicles</li>\n  <li>personal imports</li>\n  <li>amateur built vehicles (kit cars)</li>\n  <li>rebuilt vehicles</li>\n  <li>very low volume production vehicles</li>\n  <li>ambulances</li>\n  <li>motor caravans</li>\n  <li>hearses</li>\n  <li>armoured passenger vehicles</li>\n  <li>a vehicle manufactured using parts of a registered vehicle</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For help understanding these categories, download <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>’s guide on the <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> scheme.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Guide%20to%20the%20Individual%20Vehicle%20Approval%20(IVA)%20Scheme.pdf\" title=\"Download VOSA's guide on the IVA scheme (PDF, 1.84MB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>’s guide to the <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> scheme’ (PDF, 2.2MB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Normal <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr></h3>\n\n<p>If you don&rsquo;t meet the criteria for basic <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr>, you’ll have to apply for normal <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>This involves a more detailed inspection. Vehicles have to meet extra standards and you&rsquo;ll have to provide documentary evidence of this.</p>\n\n<h2>How to show your vehicle meets <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> standards</h2>\n\n<p>There are several ways to prove your vehicle meets <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> standards. For full details, see part 5 of <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>&rsquo;s guide to <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr>. </p>\n\n<h2>Model reports</h2>\n\n<p>One way of proving your vehicle is compliant is by showing it’s the same specification as another vehicle (a ‘master vehicle’) that’s been proved compliant. You do this using a model report. </p>\n\n<p>If a model report has already been produced for your exact model of vehicle, you may be able to use it for a fee. <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> has a list of <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.vosa.gov.uk/vosacorp/publications/modelreports/modelreports.htm\" title=\"Download list of model reports and their owners: VOSA\">model reports and their owners.</a></p>\n\n<p>Otherwise, you’ll need to pay for your own tests to be carried out. These must be done by an authorised provider of &lsquo;designated technical services&rsquo;. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Finding%20an%20Authorised%20Technical%20Service%20(IVA).pdf\" title=\"Download ‘Designated Technical Services’ (PDF, 79KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Designated Technical Services’ (PDF, 79KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>For more information on model reports, see part 11 of <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>’s guide on the <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> scheme.</p>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>You need to choose the <a href=\"/vehicle-approval/individual-vehicle-approval-application-forms\" title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval application forms\">correct application form</a> depending on your type of vehicle. Send it to the address on the form.</p>\n\n<h3>Choosing a test station</h3>\n\n<p>Your vehicle will be inspected by <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> at one of their approved test stations or Privately Owned Test Facilities (POTFs). You should say which one you want to use on your application form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/IVA%20Test%20Stations%20and%20POTFs.pdf\" title=\"Download 'IVA test stations and POTFs' (PDF, 274KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> test stations and POTFs’ (PDF, 274KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Cost of the scheme</h2>\n\n<p>You have to <a href=\"inspection-fees\" title=\"Inspection fees\">pay a fee</a> for the Vehicle and Operator Services Agency (<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>) to inspect your vehicle.</p>\n\n<h2>What happens next</h2>\n\n<p>Wherever possible, <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> will inspect your vehicle at the test location you&rsquo;ve chosen and issue an Individual Approval Certificate (<abbr title=\"Individual Approval Certificate\">IAC</abbr>) if it passes. You’ll need to use this certificate when you register your vehicle.</p>\n\n<h2>Appeal against a refusal</h2>\n\n<p>If your vehicle doesn&rsquo;t pass its inspection and you&rsquo;re not satisfied with the decision, you can appeal and have a re-examination carried out by an independent inspector. </p>\n\n<p>You must make your appeal within 14 days of the decision and you&rsquo;ll have to pay a fee. This will be refunded, either partially or fully, if your appeal is successful.</p>\n\n<p>You mustn&rsquo;t modify the vehicle before the appeal inspection. </p>\n\n<p>You can appeal by downloading and filling in the <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> notice of appeal.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.businesslink.gov.uk/Transport_files/121_IVA_Notice_of_Appeal_1110.doc\" title=\"Download 'IVA notice of appeal' (DOC, 139KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> notice of appeal’ (DOC, 139KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>For more information on appeals, see part 8 of <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>&rsquo;s guide on the <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> scheme.</p>\n\n<h2>More information</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> has produced an in-depth guide to the <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> scheme.